<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/22/GreatGrandDad/80f4bd9d-fd14-472c-b84a-a941dbda71ae/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/GreatGrandDad" title="User profile page">GreatGrandDad</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">13 November 2010 1:53AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>There is a great variety of wild mushrooms to be found here where I live in rural SE Asia.</p><p>I'll eat any of them that are being sold by villagers who have brought them to town and sit on the sidewalk outside the bus station.</p><p>It's their handed-down local knowledge that makes me safe.</p><p>I wouldn't eat any I found myself-----even if I had a book.<br>(If there's an Observer's Guide to Mushrooms, I'd treat the title literally.)</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
