					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I eat lots of wild mushrooms, usually in early autumn when my favourites are available. Ink caps don't really look much like the destroying angel described here. Only a novice would confuse them, and only a great fool would eat such a mushroom without being quite certain! You really don't have to be an expert to safely enjoy wild mushrooms, but you can't be careless either. </p><p>I feel sorry for the man featured in the article nonetheless. I'm sure that was a terrible experience!</p>
						
