                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Scary stuff, but man, you were careless (I know you know this!). The thing with the destroying angel is the very white gills and the very smooth cap. They usually have a sort of ruff/puffball thing at the base of the stem, too. Like others here I'm a bit puzzled you could confuse them with ink caps which, in my experience, really look quite different in several ways.</p><p>Still... you're a lucky guy, and your story should serve as a warning to others who like the wild mushroom experience. It totally is worth it, but only if you really learn your stuff thoroughly and never, if in the slightest doubt, take a chance.</p>
						
					</div>
