					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Simple rules for mushrooming:</p><p>1. If you are not 100% certain - don't pick 'n eat.<br>2. If you are not 100% certain - don't pick 'n eat.<br>3. If you are not 100% certain - don't pick 'n eat.</p><p><br>Secondly, the Ink Cap ain't all that great to eat. It is 'edible' - but then so is sliced cheap white bread.</p><p>Thirdly, anyone confusing an Ink Cap with a Destroying Angel shouldn't go picking wild mushrooms (and must have been asleep or stoned during that college "course in mushroom hunting").</p><p>Here in Britain we have plenty of excellent and easy to identify mushrooms like ceps (porcini), chanterelles, blewits and field mushrooms. Stick with those (But I'll be damned if I tell you where they can be found).</p>
						
