					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>@JBullocks</p><blockquote><p>For the cost of a bottle of wine a years supply of 5gm capsules of silybum marianum will not only help with that second bottle of red but apparently serve as an antidote to other liver-wreckers like this mushroom.</p></blockquote><p>I'm sure it's inadvertent, but you've made a very <b>dangerous </b>statement here. There is some evidence that Silibinin, the active component of milk thistle extract, can help with some cases of mushroom poisoning, but that's a long way from being an antidote, and I don't know if there's any evidence if it works for this particular mycotoxin.</p>
						
