					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>WARNING! WARNING! WARNING! Don't  use any of this information specifically because the variations in mushrooms are wide and DON'T APPLY ANYWHERE ELSE BUT LOCALLY!</p><p> If I used any of this information "never eat mushrooms that are white all over" "edible ink caps – white, with their caps down" ETC here in Australia, for instance. I could easily end up dead. </p><p> GET YOUR INFORMATION FROM<b> LOCAL EXPERTS</b> because the variations from mushroom -to-toadstools  and country-to-country is HUGE! The science is called mycology and you need to be an expert to tell the difference between many similar varieties!</p>
						
					</div>
