							<p>It would be nice to know, for the UK, which are the distinctive mushrooms that offer no potential for confusiion - maxsceptic1 gave a list, couldn't the Grauniad give us some pictures and advice?</p><p>I know there's an English tendency to be very afraid of anything that doesn't come from Tesco's. (Which may be one reason Tesco's is killing off markets and independent shops, IMO.) But foraging is good - it's a connection with the land; within ten minutes' walk of my house I can get blackberries, mulberries, and sometimes wild garlic, and I live in the city... However, we do need to educate people appropriately -- a pity we lost the tradition which is still very much alive in France and Italy.</p>
						
